## 5. Maintenance Level Mapping

### Authoritative Mapping Table

| Code | Railway Term | Display | Interval (km) | Tolerance | Duration | Man-Hours | Tracks | Cost |
|------|--------------|---------|---------------|-----------|----------|-----------|--------|------|
| A | PM1 | A-Check | 10,000 | +/- 2,000 | 4h | 8 | 1 | $2,500 |
| B | PM2 | B-Check | 50,000 | +/- 5,000 | 16h | 32 | 1 | $8,500 |
| C | PM3 | C-Check | 200,000 | +/- 20,000 | 72h | 160 | 1 | $45,000 |
| D | HM | D-Overhaul | 800,000 | +/- 50,000 | 480h | 1,200 | 2 | $180,000 |

#### Terminology Key

| Term | Meaning |
|------|---------|
| **PM1** | Preventive Maintenance Level 1 (Light) |
| **PM2** | Preventive Maintenance Level 2 (Intermediate) |
| **PM3** | Preventive Maintenance Level 3 (Scheduled) |
| **HM** | Heavy Maintenance / Major Overhaul |
| **OVH** | Full Overhaul / Refurbishment (resets all counters) |

### Maintenance Cascade

```
Fleet Type (e.g., Alstom Red Line)
 |
 +-- Maintenance Profile
     |
     +-- PM1 / A-Check (every 10,000 km)
     |   Duration: 4 hours
     |
     +-- PM2 / B-Check (every 50,000 km)
     |   Duration: 16 hours, INCLUDES PM1 tasks
     |
     +-- PM3 / C-Check (every 200,000 km)
     |   Duration: 72 hours, INCLUDES PM1 + PM2 tasks
     |
     +-- HM / D-Overhaul (every 800,000 km)
         Duration: 480 hours, RESETS counters
```

### Maintenance Triggers

| Trigger Type | Description | Best For |
|--------------|-------------|----------|
| Time-based | Calendar intervals | Simple assets, regulatory |
| Mileage-based | Odometer intervals (primary) | Wear-dependent components |
| Condition-based | Sensor thresholds | Critical components |
| Hybrid | Combined triggers | Most applications |

---

## 6. Domain Rules

### 6.1 Hard Constraints (Never Violate)

| ID | Rule | Rationale |
|----|------|-----------|
| HC-1 | Unfit trains NEVER assigned to service | Safety-critical |
| HC-2 | Maintenance windows are immutable | Planned downtime |
| HC-3 | Aptitude requirements are binary | Route compatibility |
| HC-4 | Depot capacity is physical | Track slots |
| HC-5 | Service cannot be cancelled for balancing | Operations > Optimization |

### 6.2 Soft Constraints (Optimize Within)

| ID | Rule | Weight |
|----|------|--------|
| SC-1 | Km balancing priority | 1000 (HIGH) |
| SC-2 | Dead running minimization | 100 (MEDIUM) |
| SC-3 | Maintenance depot proximity | 10 (LOW) |

### 6.3 Tolerance Windows

| Level | Tolerance | Overrun Warning | Critical |
|-------|-----------|-----------------|----------|
| PM1 / A-Check | +/- 2,000 km | 95% | 105% |
| PM2 / B-Check | +/- 5,000 km | 95% | 105% |
| PM3 / C-Check | +/- 20,000 km | 95% | 105% |
| HM / D-Overhaul | +/- 50,000 km | 95% | 105% |

