## 18. Interaction Patterns

### 18.1 Pan Navigation

```
User drags from A to B

        A ----------------> B

Canvas moves in OPPOSITE direction
(content appears to move with drag)
```

**Constraints:**
- Unconstrained within data bounds
- Soft-stop at edges with 10% overscan
- Snap-back animation if dragged beyond

### 18.2 Zoom Interaction

```
Scroll UP (away from user)    ->    Zoom IN (more detail)
Scroll DOWN (toward user)     ->    Zoom OUT (less detail)

Zoom anchored at cursor position
```

**Zoom Range:**

| Constant | Value | Purpose |
|----------|-------|---------|
| MIN_ZOOM | 0.1 | 20 years visible |
| MAX_ZOOM | 5.0 | 1 week visible |
| DEFAULT_ZOOM | 1.0 | 5 years visible |

### 18.3 Gesture Mapping

| Gesture | Device | Action |
|---------|--------|--------|
| Left-drag | Mouse | Pan canvas |
| Scroll wheel | Mouse | Zoom at cursor |
| Two-finger scroll | Trackpad | Pan canvas |
| Pinch | Trackpad/Touch | Zoom at center |
| Ctrl + Scroll | All | Horizontal pan |
| Shift + Scroll | All | Vertical pan |
| Double-click | All | Zoom in 2x |

### 18.4 Momentum Physics

```typescript
const FRICTION = 0.93;
const MIN_VELOCITY = 0.5;

function startMomentum(initialVelocity: { x: number; y: number }) {
  let velocity = { ...initialVelocity };

  function animate() {
    velocity.x *= FRICTION;
    velocity.y *= FRICTION;

    pan(velocity.x, velocity.y);

    const magnitude = Math.sqrt(velocity.x ** 2 + velocity.y ** 2);
    if (magnitude > MIN_VELOCITY) {
      requestAnimationFrame(animate);
    }
  }

  requestAnimationFrame(animate);
}
```

